ADCB Climbs to Highest in Month on Speculation of RHB Stake Sale

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-05-31T11:47:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/adcb-climbs-to-highest-in-month-on-speculation-of-rhb-stake-sale.html
Abu Dhabi  Commercial Bank, the United
Arab Emirates’ third-biggest bank, rose to the highest in a
month on speculation it may decide on a bidder for its 25
percent stake in Malaysian bank RHB Capital Bhd. today.  The shares rose 1.4 percent to 2.91 dirhams at the 2:00
p.m. close in Abu Dhabi today. The shares have gained 7 percent
in the past three days. The benchmark  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  gained
0.7 percent.  “It’s mostly retail investors moving on it for the last
couple of days,” said Marwan Shurrab, assistant  fund manager 
and chief trader at Dubai-based Gulfmena Alternative
Investments. The bank can use the proceeds to pay off maturing
debt and shore up liquidity, he said.  The decision on the stake sale may be made after a board
meeting on May 31,  Malaysia ’s The Star newspaper reported on May
27, citing people it didn’t identify. An official for ADCB, who
declined to be identified because of company policy, confirmed
the board meeting. He declined to disclose its agenda.  Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank has 3.3 billion dirhams ($898
million) in debt maturing in 2011, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
